## How to Run

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.12+
- Node.js 18+
- PostgreSQL (for full functionality)

### 1. Start PostgreSQL (Docker)
```bash
docker run -d --name crm-db -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -e POSTGRES_DB=crm_db -p 5432:5432 postgres:16-alpine
```

### 2. Start Backend
```bash
cd backend
python -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 --reload
```

### 3. Start Frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

### 4. Access
| URL | Description |
|---|---|
| http://localhost:5174 | React Frontend (Login → admin@demo.com / admin123) |
| http://localhost:8080/docs | FastAPI Swagger API Docs |
| http://localhost:8080/health | Health check endpoint |

---

## Multi-Tenancy

- Tenant isolation via `X-Tenant-ID` header on every API request
- Each tenant has isolated data, custom business type, and module toggles
- Business types: `insurance`, `retail`, `service`, `manufacturing`, [custom](file:///c:/Users/naveen/Desktop/anittaproject/backend/app/routers/customers.py#86-94)
- Each type has auto-mapped CRM terminology (e.g. "Lead" → "Policyholder" for insurance)

